to read the thing I like,

11:47.582 --> 11:49.376
that just further

11:47.582 --> 11:49.376
illustrates the point

11:49.376 --> 11:51.752
that we have nothing

11:49.376 --> 11:51.752
in common anymore!

11:51.752 --> 11:53.129
[everypony gasps]

11:53.129 --> 11:56.132
At least we agree on

11:53.129 --> 11:56.132
that! From now on,

11:56.132 --> 11:59.469
I'm only hanging out

11:56.132 --> 11:59.469
with ponies who "get" me.

11:59.469 --> 12:01.179
[gasps]

12:01.179 --> 12:04.891
Your drama can wait!

12:01.179 --> 12:04.891
Twilight needs help, now!

12:06.017 --> 12:09.770
[whimpers]

12:09.770 --> 12:11.064
Any luck?

12:11.064 --> 12:14.568
No! It's gone!

12:14.568 --> 12:15.860
What's gone?

12:15.860 --> 12:18.279
The Amulet of Aurora.

12:18.279 --> 12:19.989
One of the magical items

12:18.279 --> 12:19.989
you've been keeping

12:19.989 --> 12:21.658
for Princess Celestia?

12:21.658 --> 12:25.119
That amulet can reverse the

12:21.658 --> 12:25.119
tides and summon tsunamis!

12:25.119 --> 12:27.163
If it falls into the

12:25.119 --> 12:27.163
wrong hooves,

12:27.163 --> 12:30.667
Equestria will be

12:27.163 --> 12:30.667
in grave danger!

12:30.667 --> 12:31.792
Don't worry, Twilight!

12:31.792 --> 12:34.713
I know tons about searching

12:31.792 --> 12:34.713
for lost treasure!

12:34.713 --> 12:36.631
And if I follow the

12:34.713 --> 12:36.631
culprit's clues,

12:36.631 --> 12:38.717
I'm certain I can find

12:36.631 --> 12:38.717
who took your amulet!

12:40.301 --> 12:42.345
Thank you! I'll

12:40.301 --> 12:42.345
feel so much better

12:42.345 --> 12:45.515
knowing you two are

12:42.345 --> 12:45.515
looking for it together.

12:46.641 --> 12:48.518
While we work on

12:46.641 --> 12:48.518
a locator spell!

12:48.518 --> 12:49.768
It's the perfect solution!

12:54.441 --> 12:56.775
There appear to be

12:54.441 --> 12:56.775
no signs of damage

12:56.775 --> 12:58.777
to the surrounding artifacts,

12:58.777 --> 13:01.780
suggesting the thief

12:58.777 --> 13:01.780
did not leave in a hurry.

13:07.287 --> 13:10.789
Rarity! Your boots are leaving

13:07.287 --> 13:10.789
sparkles all over the floor!

13:12.833 --> 13:19.840
Those aren't from my

13:12.833 --> 13:19.840
boots. Mine are magenta,

13:12.833 --> 13:19.840
not blue. See?

13:19.840 --> 13:20.799
[gasp]

13:22.469 --> 13:24.095
I mean, really!

13:27.848 --> 13:30.851
[whimpering]

13:30.851 --> 13:33.854
Turns out these boots were

13:30.851 --> 13:33.854
not "made for trotting,"

13:33.854 --> 13:35.398
as advertised.

13:37.651 --> 13:41.862
Where are you going?

13:37.651 --> 13:41.862
We promised Twilight

13:37.651 --> 13:41.862
we'd work together.

13:41.862 --> 13:43.490
Don't you see?

13:43.490 --> 13:46.701
The Amulet of Aurora is

13:43.490 --> 13:46.701
made out of Azurantium!

13:49.287 --> 13:51.830
Azurantium? You know,

13:49.287 --> 13:51.830
the same metal

13:51.830 --> 13:53.374
that the Amulet of Atonement

13:53.374 --> 13:55.376
from Daring Do Book

13:53.374 --> 13:55.376
4 is made from?

13:55.376 --> 13:57.796
It always leaves sparkles

13:55.376 --> 13:57.796
wherever it goes!

13:57.796 --> 14:02.467
Just like this. Remember? It's

13:57.796 --> 14:02.467
from the book you just read?

14:02.467 --> 14:08.723
[nervous chuckle]

14:02.467 --> 14:08.723
That book yes. The one

14:02.467 --> 14:08.723
I-I just read. Heh.

14:09.641 --> 14:13.478
Seriously? After giving

14:09.641 --> 14:13.478
me all that grief,

14:13.478 --> 14:16.230
you didn't read

14:13.478 --> 14:16.230
mine either?

14:16.230 --> 14:18.817
Oopsie?

14:18.817 --> 14:22.487
As soon as we find this

14:18.817 --> 14:22.487
amulet, we are done

14:18.817 --> 14:22.487
with each other.

14:23.904 --> 14:25.615
Fine by me!

14:30.328 --> 14:32.580
♪♪

14:32.580 --> 14:34.165
[panting]

14:36.917 --> 14:42.716
Rainbow Dash, slow down!

14:36.917 --> 14:42.716
You're flying past

14:36.917 --> 14:42.716
important clues!

14:42.716 --> 14:45.301
It's a print. but

14:42.716 --> 14:45.301
definitely not a hoof.

14:45.301 --> 14:46.927
Are those claw marks?

14:46.927 --> 14:49.889
Who cares? I found

14:46.927 --> 14:49.889
a bigger clue.

14:54.310 --> 14:55.936
I hope you don't

14:54.310 --> 14:55.936
expect me to...

14:55.936 --> 14:58.898
[shudder] wade through that.

15:05.488 --> 15:08.700
Nah, it's too deep.

15:05.488 --> 15:08.700
We'll get stuck.

15:08.700 --> 15:11.952
Clever! What Daring Do book

15:08.700 --> 15:11.952
did you get that from?

15:11.952 --> 15:14.748
Actually, I learned it at

15:11.952 --> 15:14.748
Scootaloo's Filly Guides camp.

15:16.457 --> 15:18.251
At least you can fly across.

15:19.627 --> 15:23.964
[explosions and shouts]

15:23.964 --> 15:26.967
Nope! If one of those geysers

15:23.964 --> 15:26.967
burns off my wingfeathers,

15:26.967 --> 15:30.889
I'll be out of the

15:26.967 --> 15:30.889
Wonderbolts for weeks.

15:30.889 --> 15:33.933
I could try and

15:30.889 --> 15:33.933
slingshot my way through,

15:33.933 --> 15:35.894
but I'd need two

15:33.933 --> 15:35.894
perfectly placed trees,

15:35.894 --> 15:37.937
some stretchy rope,

15:35.894 --> 15:37.937
and a pith helmet.

15:39.898 --> 15:41.982
Too bad we can't

15:39.898 --> 15:41.982
do what Daring Do did

15:41.982 --> 15:44.985
in book 4 and find a

15:41.982 --> 15:44.985
Cragadile for a raft.

15:44.985 --> 15:49.407
Ta da! The SS Cragadile,

15:44.985 --> 15:49.407
at your service.

15:50.784 --> 15:54.662
Uh, that is awesome!

15:54.662 --> 15:57.916
I mean... it's all

15:54.662 --> 15:57.916
right. I guess.

16:00.501 --> 16:02.670
How did you know

16:00.501 --> 16:02.670
how to do that?

16:02.670 --> 16:05.715
We may have been friends

16:02.670 --> 16:05.715
"for a super long time,"

16:05.715 --> 16:07.967
but you don't know

16:05.715 --> 16:07.967
everything about me yet!

16:18.645 --> 16:21.021
The glitter trail! It's gone!

16:21.021 --> 16:24.484
How are we supposed to find

16:21.021 --> 16:24.484
the Amulet of Aurora now?

16:24.484 --> 16:28.529
[rustling]

16:28.529 --> 16:30.030
[croak]

16:30.030 --> 16:31.616
[shrill scream]

16:31.616 --> 16:36.830
[very quietly] Ow, ears!

16:31.616 --> 16:36.830
Why hoof-hoofs yell?

16:36.830 --> 16:39.332
Too-too loud.

16:40.040 --> 16:43.043
Sorry, what did you say?

16:43.043 --> 16:47.047
Too-too loud.

16:47.047 --> 16:50.927
I think it's a Bufogren! They

16:47.047 --> 16:50.927
have really sensitive ears.

16:50.927 --> 16:53.012
Did you happen to

16:50.927 --> 16:53.012
see anycreature

16:53.012 --> 16:56.056
with a sparkly

16:53.012 --> 16:56.056
thingy go this way?

16:56.056 --> 16:57.600
Saw it.

16:57.600 --> 17:00.060
Gah!

17:00.060 --> 17:01.020
Hold that thought.

17:07.026 --> 17:10.780
His breath smells so

17:07.026 --> 17:10.780
bad I can't think!

17:10.780 --> 17:15.034
But we can't hear him

17:10.780 --> 17:15.034
from back here. Now what?

17:15.034 --> 17:16.786
Hmm.

17:18.454 --> 17:20.790
[sniffing]

17:20.790 --> 17:24.669
Hah! I think I have

17:20.790 --> 17:24.669
the perfect solution.

17:24.669 --> 17:28.631
An old unicorn beauty trick.

17:24.669 --> 17:28.631
That is, if you can somehow

17:28.631 --> 17:30.633
procure us a tiny

17:28.631 --> 17:30.633
bit of cloud?

17:30.633 --> 17:32.051
Now that! I can do!

17:38.683 --> 17:40.393
It's adorable!

17:46.983 --> 17:49.777
Excuse me, kind sir.

17:49.777 --> 17:52.071
I have a special

17:49.777 --> 17:52.071
treat for you

17:52.071 --> 17:54.574
in exchange

17:52.071 --> 17:54.574
for your information.

17:56.534 --> 17:59.704
What's that?

17:59.704 --> 18:02.957
It is a magical

17:59.704 --> 18:02.957
Unicorn delicacy

18:02.957 --> 18:04.792
called "Effervescence."

18:04.792 --> 18:07.086
Very now, very chic.

18:08.713 --> 18:10.048
Ooow!

18:10.048 --> 18:12.091
Sorry. Sorry. Enjoy!

18:14.928 --> 18:18.973
Muh mouth. Fresh and minty.

18:22.142 --> 18:28.900
Good! Now which way did

18:22.142 --> 18:28.900
the sparkly thing go?

18:28.900 --> 18:32.152
Up-up! Up there.

18:32.152 --> 18:33.153
Thank you!

18:35.155 --> 18:37.784
Well, what are you

18:35.155 --> 18:37.784
waiting for? Go on!

18:37.784 --> 18:40.912
Fly up there and

18:37.784 --> 18:40.912
get that amulet!

18:40.912 --> 18:43.539
We're doing this

18:40.912 --> 18:43.539
together, remember?

18:43.539 --> 18:45.041
But how can we? Oh!

18:45.041 --> 18:50.129
[panicked whimpers]

18:50.129 --> 18:53.591
Sorry, but I wasn't leaving

18:50.129 --> 18:53.591
you behind in that swamp.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.719
Thank you.

18:56.719 --> 19:00.556
♪♪

19:00.556 --> 19:03.017
[knocking]

19:03.017 --> 19:04.978
Maybe the key to

19:03.017 --> 19:04.978
unlocking this thing

19:04.978 --> 19:07.563
is in these inscriptions.

19:07.563 --> 19:10.566
Or perhaps the

19:07.563 --> 19:10.566
key is right here.

19:10.566 --> 19:13.486
♪♪

19:13.486 --> 19:15.696
I couldn't decide between

19:13.486 --> 19:15.696
the boots and the stilettos,

19:15.696 --> 19:17.156
so I got both.

19:20.200 --> 19:22.202
High heels can

19:20.200 --> 19:22.202
do that?

19:22.202 --> 19:25.205
And you called

19:22.202 --> 19:25.205
them useless.

19:25.205 --> 19:28.167
I shouldn't have said that.

19:25.205 --> 19:28.167
Or made fun of the other stuff

19:28.167 --> 19:32.212
you like to do. Some of

19:28.167 --> 19:32.212
it's actually sorta neat.

19:32.212 --> 19:35.215
I owe you an apology, too.

19:35.215 --> 19:39.219
Buckball may not be my thing,

19:35.215 --> 19:39.219
but it's something you enjoy.

19:39.219 --> 19:41.221
And you're very good at it!

19:41.221 --> 19:43.182
I never should have

19:41.221 --> 19:43.182
treated your interests

19:43.182 --> 19:45.810
like they were worth

19:43.182 --> 19:45.810
less than mine.

19:45.810 --> 19:49.981
So... does this mean

19:45.810 --> 19:49.981
we're still friends?

19:49.981 --> 19:53.026
I would very

19:49.981 --> 19:53.026
much like that.

19:53.026 --> 19:55.235
Now let's go find

19:53.026 --> 19:55.235
that amulet!

19:55.235 --> 19:56.654
Yeah! Ha ha!

20:00.240 --> 20:04.244
Wait. That tunnel

20:00.240 --> 20:04.244
leads to the school?

20:04.244 --> 20:07.206
A secret passage!

20:04.244 --> 20:07.206
Awesone!

20:08.666 --> 20:14.130
[gasp] Spikey-Wikey, you

20:08.666 --> 20:14.130
stole the Amulet of Aurora?

20:14.130 --> 20:16.090
[Twilight] Not exactly.

20:18.258 --> 20:22.930
You mean... this was a

20:18.258 --> 20:22.930
setup to make us get along?

20:22.930 --> 20:26.266
Sorry to interfere,

20:22.930 --> 20:26.266
but you both--

20:26.266 --> 20:28.686
Really needed it.

20:28.686 --> 20:32.023
[laughter]

20:32.023 --> 20:35.275
So even though you don't like

20:32.023 --> 20:35.275
any of the same stuff,

20:35.275 --> 20:38.278
you two are friends again?

20:38.278 --> 20:43.283
Always. I think we just

20:38.278 --> 20:43.283
needed a teensy reminder.

20:43.283 --> 20:46.286
Yeah. We don't have to

20:43.283 --> 20:46.286
love the exact same things

20:46.286 --> 20:49.707
to have fun together. I

20:46.286 --> 20:49.707
mean, imagine if we did.

20:49.707 --> 20:52.292
How boring would that be?

20:52.292 --> 20:54.628
When we give each other

20:52.292 --> 20:54.628
a chance to share the

20:52.292 --> 20:54.628
different things

20:54.628 --> 20:59.175
we enjoy, it can be

20:54.628 --> 20:59.175
surprisingly wonderful!

20:59.175 --> 21:02.053
Too bad we wasted

20:59.175 --> 21:02.053
our Day of Fun.

21:02.053 --> 21:03.930
We still have a

21:02.053 --> 21:03.930
little time left!

21:03.930 --> 21:06.099
You wanna... go hit the shops?

21:06.099 --> 21:07.307
I could actually

21:06.099 --> 21:07.307
use your help

21:07.307 --> 21:08.851
picking out some

21:07.307 --> 21:08.851
new Buckball gear!

21:08.851 --> 21:10.310
Do I?

21:10.310 --> 21:14.107
But only if you help me choose

21:10.310 --> 21:14.107
some Buckball fan attire,

21:14.107 --> 21:16.109
so I can cheer for

21:14.107 --> 21:16.109
my favorite player

21:16.109 --> 21:18.152
at the drop of a fabulous hat.

21:18.152 --> 21:20.947
Uh, yeah! Let's go already!

21:20.947 --> 21:23.323
[happy chatter]

21:23.323 --> 21:28.121
See? Good friends always work

21:23.323 --> 21:28.121
through their differences.

21:28.121 --> 21:30.790
Even if it takes

21:28.121 --> 21:30.790
a little help.

21:34.501 --> 21:37.546
♪♪
